## Decisions made this session
- Build tool: Maven multi-module monorepo + shared `common` module
- Concurrency guard: Redis lock + Postgres `@Version` optimistic locking
- Outbox: scheduled relay poller (`FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`), not Debezium
- Dashboard transport: SSE (endpoint exists on order-service; full UI in M4)
- Frontend: dashboard at `/`, no auth, no landing page
- Deviations approved: no LLM layer, all-local Docker Compose, no auth/landing
- Persistence style: idiomatic Spring Data (`OrderRepository`), no adapter boilerplate
- Delivery: at-least-once + idempotency; virtual threads deferred (not wired in M1)
- **Additive contract (M1 demo):** `Simulate.failAfterReserve` on `PlaceOrderRequest` / `CommandMessage`
- **M3 CB config:** Resilience4j `@CircuitBreaker` on `ShipmentService.create`; slow-call threshold 2s; opens after 60% fail rate in 5-call window; `waitDurationInOpenState: 10s`
- **M4 frontend stack:** Vite + React + Tailwind with SSE-first dashboard at `/` (no auth/landing, per D-16)
- **M4 observability stack:** Zipkin + Prometheus + Grafana wired into Compose; Spring Micrometer+OTel enabled across all services
- **M4 dashboard metrics:** Added `orderflow.orders.placed|confirmed|failed` counters in order-service for throughput/success-failure panels
- **M5 traceability hardening:** Persist `traceparent` in outbox headers, replay headers in relay publishes, enable listener observation on custom factories, tag spans with `order.id`/`saga.id`

